    narrator "{i}The failures cascade through the morning shift. Small at first-a calibration tool that won't zero, a welding torch that sparks when it should flame, a cart that refuses to move in one direction but rolls fine in the other.{/i}"
    narrator "{i}And one that isn't mechanical at all: Grinder 7 skips. Not the machine-the {i}sound{/i}. It grinds, stops, and then the noise arrives a half-second late, like audio dragged through water. Everyone on the line freezes. Avyanna tastes copper. A worker near the railing taps twice, reflexive, not thinking about it. The moment passes. They go back to work.{/i}"
    narrator "{i}Then bigger.{/i}"
